execution_environment.label: Execution environment

id.name: id
id.label: ID
id.description: Database ID for this job template.

job_slice_count.name: job_slice_count
job_slice_count.label: Job slice count
job_slice_count.description: The number of jobs to slice into at runtime. Will cause the Job Template to launch a workflow if value is greater than 1.

organization.name: organization
organization.label: Organization
organization.description: The organization used to determine access to this template.

prevent_instance_group_fallback.name: prevent_instance_group_fallback
prevent_instance_group_fallback.label: Prevent instance group fallback
prevent_instance_group_fallback.description: If enabled, the job template will prevent adding any inventory or organization instance groups to the list of preferred instances groups to run on.If this setting is enabled and you provided an empty list, the global instance groups will be applied.

scm_branch.name: scm_branch
scm_branch.label: Scm branch
scm_branch.description: Branch to use in job run. Project default used if blank. Only allowed if project allow_override field is set to true.

timeout.name: timeout
timeout.label: Timeout
timeout.description: The amount of time (in seconds) to run before the task is canceled.

use_fact_cache.name: use_fact_cache
use_fact_cache.label: Use fact cache
use_fact_cache.description: If enabled, the service will act as an Ansible Fact Cache Plugin; persisting facts at the end of a playbook run to the database and caching facts for use by Ansible.

webhook_credential.name: webhook_credential
webhook_credential.label: Webhook credential
webhook_credential.description: Personal Access Token for posting back the status to the service API

webhook_service.name: webhook_service
webhook_service.label: Webhook service
webhook_service.description: Service that webhook requests will be accepted from
